CLIENT:
npm run start
npm i axios

(Create-react-app creates a git repo, delete with ls -a, rm -fr .git)


BACKEND:
npm init -y
nom i express body-parser corn mongoose
nodemon server
Create .gitignore, put in node_modules

MONGODB STUFF
set up server connection with : 
    mongod 

new terminal: set up database
    mongo
    use <db name, ex: boilers>

Now you'll see connection established successfully with server.js

Test endpoints with postman

